https://github.com/openbmc/phosphor-dbus-interfaces/blob/a1347418307d31a94bd21f22897aa508df938dcf/yaml/xyz/openbmc_project/Inventory/Item.interface.yaml#L36-L43

If SBTSI is a CPU sensor, should it be in CPU sensor daemon?
What is the redfish URI for this? Please add.

> If SBTSI is a CPU sensor, should it be in CPU sensor daemon?

1. I don't find CPU sensor daemon in `dbus-sensors` (except IntelCPUSensor that is specifically for Intel).
2. This sensor is a qualified hwmon sensor. I am unsure what's the benefit for handling it separately since we can handle it as a normal hwmon sensor.

> What is the redfish URI for this? Please add.

Added in the end of `Tested`
The URI will be like `"@odata.id": "/redfish/v1/Systems/system/Processors/cpu0"`
Ack
This is system specific, which should be defined in a system specific config file

Not really..
`SBTSI` is for AMD CPU only. It must be CPU sensor no matter which system you are using.

findInventoryPath can return null string. 
Is it fine to initialize HwmonTempSensor object in this case?
Or should it be treated as error?

Empty string is okay.
We handle this case in `HwmonTempSensor.cpp` (https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/dbus-sensors/+/60031/9/src/HwmonTempSensor.cpp#80)
